title: James Francis
text:
James Francis


CONTACT: | My Email | My LinkedIn


Education

September 2023 - Present
Bachelors of Science Degree, Computer Science
Cumulative GPA: 4.0



Experience

Melaleuca
January 2024 - July 2024
Customer Care Specialist | Rexburg, Idaho
- Resolved 50+ customer inquiries per shift, troubleshooting technical issues, product questions, and service-related concerns, ensuring a 90% first-call resolution rate. - Collaborated with cross-functional teams by escalating complex issues, documenting 100% of interactions with detailed notes, contributing to seamless customer experiences. - Consistently ranked in the top 10 among peers by exceeding performance metrics, improving customer satisfaction scores by 15%, and sharing best practices to enhance team performance.


The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints
August 2021 - August 2023
Volunteer Representative | Layton, Utah
- Developed proficiency in building and managing interpersonal relationships.
- Designed spreadsheets to supervise and analyze volunteer efforts for 50+ representatives in 8+ cities.
- Raised productivity through interactive training to large groups in 40+ meetings.


Indiana Lawn Pros
May 2021 - August 2021
Logistics Specialist | Bloomington, Indiana
- Improved working relationships with 50+ clients, boosting overall revenue.
- Processed and delivered 750+ invoices to 100+ clients over 4 months.
- Enforced compliance with federal regulations at 600+ job sites, ensuring the safety of both team members and clients.


McLean Maintenance
May 2019 - August 2020
Landscape Designer | Bloomington, Indiana
- Designed and maintained 40+ private and public spaces, both indoor and outdoor.
- Interfaced with 50+ clients individually during maintenance requests, fielding inquiries regarding design optimizations.


Computer Repair - Bloomington High School North
August 2018 - June 2020
Technical Lead | Bloomington, Indiana
- Provided highly technical customer service to 750+ people, troubleshooting software and hardware issues.
- Managed, updated, and repaired both software and hardware of a fleet of 1750+ school devices, extensively using a service ticketing system.
- Developed technical abilities of 20+ team members through personalized training, increasing productivity and overall performance.
